@landong1973 - dividing duration is not currently supported. No reason it can be added, it just hasn't been done.

Contributions welcome!

Recorded as https://github.com/apache/jena/issues/2273

Thank you. I upgraded to jena 4.10.0, but I am a bit skeptic to using 5.0.0, since it is only a release candidate (rc1).

The following code works:
```
    public static String convertToTurtle(Model description) {
        try (ByteArrayOutputStream modelWriter = new ByteArrayOutputStream();) {
        RDFWriter.source(description)
                 .format(RDFFormat.TURTLE)
                 .output(modelWriter);
            return modelWriter.toString(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);
        } catch (IOException e) {
            throw new NrkTechnicalException("Failed to serialize model as TURTLE", e);
        }
    }
```
